cs_siege_sp
 by splaty (splaty@zyon.org)

cs_siege was my favourite map, and so here it is, in its (I hope) glory on counter-strike: source.

I aimed to keep it as close to the original as possible, since in my opinion, cs_siege had great gameplay, even if it was a bit cramped.

The bots also have full waypoints and are reasonably smart. They don't go into the mines since they can't use the elevator (maybe one day..) but they will vary their routes through the sewers or the main tunnel. And, of course, the Ts will tend to camp in a variety of places around the garage.

Hope you all have as much time playing it as I did making it (which was a fair bit)!
This is thé cs_siege map the way its suposed to be.

Cs_siege_pcs
Created by Dimension Studios
www.dimensionstudios.org
======================
Map Author: Rickets007
email: Rickets007@gmail.com 

This map is a remake of the Counter-Strike 1.x map cs_siege but with several additions. I wanted to keep the feel of this map as close to the original cs_siege as possible. I kept the same layout as in the original map but added to the inner complex almost doubling its size. Furthermore, I reworked the sewer system to be less linear and included two additional access points. The two original hostage rooms are the same but there is a third location where the hostages can spawn. The four hostages randomly spawn in two of the three rooms each round. Rather than doing a traditional overview of the map I opted to create a blueprint style drawing using AutoCAD. It really creates a nice effect and allows for easier navigation for players unfamiliar with the map. To further help navigation and to aid in the rescue of the hostages, the water in the sewer flows away from the base. Just follow it and you will get to the rescue point.

CS_SCREW by Prabab / Kamil Wolter (released May 2011)

"This map, while using a simple concept, is perfectly done. The various small levels composing it are all connected to a central pit. With a layout such as this, set aside your old habits and quickly learn to look up and down. If you don't, you won't live long.

As the map is very small, the rounds will not last long. It is impossible to be lost as every passages lead to the central pit... where everyone life-span is short, very short.

And don't forget: we are in CS:S, so you can fall from any height into 2 inches of water and you won't take any damage at all."

- from review at NetDay.be

About Playing with Bots: NAV-file for playing against the Bots (embedded in .bsp-file) are more or less playable, though isn't optimized manually.

Overview: cs_school takes place at a community college technical center. It has been designed to include multiple entrances, 
defensive positions, and contact points.

Beta2 Fixes/additions: 
- Addressed FPS lag issues. Map has been optimized.
- Set the Power Box turn off all lights in the complex.
- Added a vent access to the bathroom.
- Repositioned the hostages to be more fair to the Counter-Terrorists.
- Cleaned up several cracks in the map textures.
- Added several grass decals in the alley.

-CT Spawn: Offers 3 initial paths of assault (Alley, Front Entrance, Truck Crash), all with distinct advantages and disadvantages.
-T Spawn: Gives the Terrorist team an array of defensive positions (Classroom windows, Bathrooms, Doorways, Light Powerbox) 
and environmental elements to encourage them.
-Alley: Focuses on straight forward duck-and-cover fighting; enhanced with multiple areas of escape.
-Front Entrance: Provides cover for the Terrorists and is best used by Counter-Terrorists if roof support is available.
-Truck Crash: Supplies the Counter-Terrorists with a speedy means of assault, at the cost of cover.
-Roof: Accessed by the Alley, allows the Counter-Terrorists a skylight advantage point and passage to a hostage room via a vent.
-Bathrooms: A hostage is held here and can be defended by awaiting Terrorists in the stalls.
-Custodial Hallway: Connected to the Alley by the back door, this hallway provides cover for both Counter-Terrorists and
Terrorists. It also contains a Powerbox which may be used to turn off the lights in the Front Entrance.

Notes: Thanks for downloading.I attempted to balance the gameplay factors as much as possible, but as this is my first map feel 
free to contact me with  suggestions and criticisms (constructive or otherwise).

	- Weathers
MSN: Weathers404@hotmail.com
Steam: Weathers404
Have fun and Pm me if your have any questions, :)

The setting of this map is a Rocket Silo as well as some attached underground areas. Aside from the rocket silo you will also find the corresponding command center as well as a helicopter landing platform.
The starting point for the CTs is placed right next to this landing platform while the Hostage Area as well as the Ts' starting point is located inside of the facility.
The hostages have to be led outside either towards the blue trailer next to landing spot or towards the rocket silo itself.
Because the map was design for LAN-Partys with at least 20 Players, I put in several ways to save the hostages to give it a more tactical approach than many other CS Maps.
Due to the fact that I put quite some effort into the visual appeal of the map, it should ideally be run on a computer with at least a Dual Core CPU and something equal or greater to a Geforce 8600.

Now, just go and have fun with it.
